  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building adaptation and resilience to climate change in the essential oil sector in Madagascar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project has been endorsed by the Country GEF OFP on 1 July 2020 for submission to the GEF LDCF. The project objective is to reduce vulnerability and increasing resilience to climate change of the essential oils value chain by promoting innovation, transfer and large-scale deployment of adaptation-oriented technologies and services. The project will pilot and support MSMEs with proof-of-concept climate adaptation-oriented technologies and create enabling conditions for large-scale deployment of the technologies by applying UNIDO#s unique approach. Through integrating resilience building and innovation for climate-adaptation, the proposed interventions will transform the EO sector and unleash rural economic development with a major potential for scaling up sustainably and offering a significant benefit to communities in some regions of Madagascar.</narrative>
  </description>
